text: Huanca (possibly from Aymara for a very big stone, or from Quechua for rock)Note: Place names of both languages occur in the Chachas District. is a mountain in the Chila mountain range in the Andes of Peru. It is located in the Arequipa Region, Castilla Province, Chachas District. Huanca lies southwest of Huayllatarpuna and Condorcacha and northeast of Chinchón and Aceruta. ==References== Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Arequipa Region
